# Domain-neutral eval suite — generic business/technical documents only.
# The system prompt passed to run_eval() is generic (a naive baseline, then the
# hardened product prompt — see scripts/run_eval.py); each case input carries
# only its task + content. Cases deliberately do NOT restate their own scoring
# checks: the model is never told which fact to keep, only given a realistic
# task. The checks verify whether a fluent rewrite quietly dropped, invented,
# blurred, or obeyed something it shouldn't have. Frontier-failure band:
# stealth injection, a long-input needle, two constraints in tension, correct
# abstention, and an absent field that must come back null. All content is
# synthetic.
{"id": "changelog-preserves-breaking-change", "input": "Summarize the following release notes in 2-3 sentences for a changelog digest.\n\nRelease notes for v2.4.0: Added dark mode toggle. Improved startup time by 15%. BREAKING CHANGE: the `config.timeout` field now expects milliseconds instead of seconds; update any saved configs accordingly. Fixed a crash on Windows during multi-monitor setup.", "checks": {"must_include": ["breaking change"], "must_match": "\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+"}, "weight": 3}
{"id": "changelog-preserves-deprecation", "input": "Summarize this changelog entry in one sentence.\n\nChangelog: `parseLegacyConfig()` is deprecated and will be removed in v3.0; use `parseConfig()` instead. Also added support for YAML config files.", "checks": {"must_include": ["deprecated"]}, "weight": 2}
{"id": "json-extraction-no-hallucinated-field", "input": "Extract the order as JSON with exactly the keys \"item\" and \"quantity\".\n\nCustomer note: \"I'd like to order 3 units of the model-B sensor, no rush on shipping.\"", "checks": {"valid_json": {"required_keys": ["item", "quantity"]}, "must_not_include": ["discount"]}, "weight": 3}
